Package: btrfsnapd
Architecture: amd64
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 btrfs-progs, systemd, coreutils (>= 8), grub-common, grub2-common, grub-btrfsd
Conflicts: btrfsnapd (>= 2.2.2), btrfsnapd-man
Description:  Btrfs snapshot daemon
 Btrfsnapd is a daemon that manages Btrfs snapshots and integrates with
 GRUB to allow booting into snapshots. It provides a simple command-line
 interface for creating, listing, and deleting snapshots, as well as
 restoring the system to a previous state.
 .
 This package is designed to work with Btrfs filesystems and requires
 btrfs-progs to function correctly.

Package: btrfsnapd-docs
Architecture: all
Depends: btrfsnapd
Description: Documentation for Btrfsnapd
 This package contains the documentation for Btrfsnapd, including user guides,
 manuals, and other relevant information to help users understand and utilize the
 features of Btrfsnapd effectively. It is intended to provide comprehensive information
 about the installation, configuration, and usage of Btrfsnapd for users of all levels
 of expertise.
